      title: 'Design Your Own Superhero',
      description: 'Give each child a blank hero template showing an outline figure in a dynamic pose. Children design their hero by drawing a costume, choosing colors, and adding a symbol or logo. On the back, they write or dictate the hero\'s name, superpower, and one sentence about how the hero helps others. Display the heroes on a classroom wall. This activity reinforces descriptive vocabulary, creative expression, and the character trait discussions from worksheets while developing fine motor skills and design thinking.',
